name: Parmesan Focaccia Bread
author: Sandra Bennett
summary: A delicious savory round loaf, with parmesan and olive oil.
ingredients: 1 ⅓ cups warm water (110 degrees F/45 degrees C)
directions: Place ingredients (except 1/3 cup olive oil and Parmesan cheese) in the bread machine in the order suggested by the manufacturer
When the dough has risen once in the breadmaker, transfer it into an oiled, 8-inch round baking tin
Allow to rise until doubled in bulk
Poke it all over with your finger, right to the bottom of the tin
Allow to rest for another 5 to 10 minutes
Pour 1/3 cup olive oil over the top of the loaf, and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese
Bake at 400 degrees F (205 degrees C) in center of oven for approximately 20 minutes, until golden
